11.body: Shows your user name, and what current network activity is occuring. (Usually quiescent ). Click on sync status to see the error log. Note that data is saved locally. It is also sent to the server (and vise versa) periodically.

12.body: For pieces with a picture, the thumbnail is a fast way to click and select the piece. You can then inspect and edit data on that piece. When a piece is selected, images of that piece are shown instead of all thumbnails.
12.breadcrumbs: Explain the Display » Thumbnail buttons / Images

13.body: The Main Menu is the primary point for navigating to the many program features. The Home button (upper left icon) always takes you here. The Main Menu page shares all the features of the standard Page Display with feature buttons on top, status and Thumbnails. The focus of the page is:
13.title: Main Menu

14.body: Lists of your pieces organized in different ways New Piece to create an entry for a new piece Instructions for overall help Name/Password to modify your credentials to the database Advanced Options informational but not normally needed in general usage
14.title: Menu Choices

15.body: This page offers a choice of various ways to list your pieces. Lists are sortable tables of the pieces with thumbnail pictures. Note you can also choose from the pictures below, or search for specific text. Left Column All Pieces New Piece to add a new creation. Right Column The pieces are grouped by one of: Series , Firing , Clay , Glaze A piece may appear in more than one group.
15.title: List Menu

2.body: Potholder is a web-based program that lets you keep track of your ceramic pieces. It works well on phones, laptops and tablets, and will synchronize automatically between all the devices when it can. The database includes images, kiln and glaze data, and other production processes. You don't have to install anything -- it's all there in the web page. You don't even have to be on-line to use it.
2.title: Summary

20.body: Rather than one long list, your pieces can be listed by Groups like "Clay", "Glaze", "Series", "Firing", etc. The available choices are seen in the List Menu .
20.breadcrumbs: List Menu » Grouped List » Grouped List
20.title: Grouped List

21.body: You can see this grouping is by "Clay," and the name of each clay found is shown.
21.title: Groups

22.body: Each group is a separate table. You can select a piece to inspect or edit by clicking on it's row in the table.
22.breadcrumbs: List Menu » Grouped List » Separate Lists
22.title: Separate Lists

26.body: This picture button brings u0p either the camera (phone) or the gallery (laptop). Since no piece is currently selected, you will have to choose the destination: The choices are either A new piece. (The data entry screen will then be presented). An existing piece. 48.body: Note: This is an advanced internal view. It is not essential for using the program. Basically the Error Log can be helpful for showing problems with the program or the network. Messages are shown one per line, with colored striping to help separate them. Erase Log will clear the messages, but cause no other issue.
48.title: Error Log
